WEBVTT

00:08.441 --> 00:11.310

Previously on


00:08.441 --> 00:11.310

<i>One Dollar...</i>


00:08.441 --> 00:11.310

<i>What did you do to your wife?</i>


00:11.343 --> 00:12.478

I dont have a wife.


00:11.343 --> 00:12.478

Bullshit.


00:12.512 --> 00:14.314

I went to Mercy Seat.


00:12.512 --> 00:14.314

Dannie!


00:14.346 --> 00:15.348

Thats my sister!


00:15.381 --> 00:17.182

<i>Carries my niece.</i>


00:17.216 --> 00:19.251

<i>W-We got to be square,
because I dont, I dont think</i>


00:19.285 --> 00:20.519

<i>we should ever
see each other again.</i>


00:20.553 --> 00:22.388

CHELSEA:<i>
I found some checks,</i>


00:22.422 --> 00:23.722

<i>which made me curious,
so I started snooping.</i>


00:23.757 --> 00:25.658

<i>You treated me like the mark,</i>


00:25.692 --> 00:28.128

and I told you
that Im not the mark.


00:28.161 --> 00:30.362

You want in?


00:28.161 --> 00:30.362

Yeah.


00:30.396 --> 00:31.731

HENCHMAN:<i>
We know who you are.</i>


00:31.765 --> 00:35.301

Whatever you do,
well know about it.


00:35.335 --> 00:37.270

JAKE:


00:35.335 --> 00:37.270

<i>I dont have any idea
who those people were</i>


00:37.302 --> 00:38.604

<i>or why they did that to me.</i>


00:38.637 --> 00:40.439

Maybe I just let this one die.


00:40.472 --> 00:41.807

Thought we were having
a good time.


00:41.841 --> 00:43.475

I mean, I havent heard
from you.


00:43.509 --> 00:44.878

<i>Look, its pretty clear
that you have</i>


00:44.911 --> 00:46.679

<i>some shit going on.</i>


00:46.713 --> 00:47.847

<i>Call me when youre done.</i>


00:51.518 --> 00:53.118

RICK:<i>
Youre doing all this
for a contract?</i>


00:53.152 --> 00:54.219

BUD:<i>
Im having to beg, borrow</i>


00:54.253 --> 00:56.588

and steal for something that
should be ours by right.


00:56.622 --> 00:58.323

FOOTLONG:
Nobody move.


00:58.357 --> 00:59.526

GOOT:
Youre with them?


01:03.396 --> 01:05.597

You might have ruined
the whole thing.


01:03.396 --> 01:05.597

Im sorry, Pop.


01:24.384 --> 01:27.519

Hey, buddy.
Could you help us out?


01:27.554 --> 01:29.656

Sorry. We-we dont need
any money.


01:29.688 --> 01:32.192

Its just our battery died.


01:32.224 --> 01:33.793

You have any, uh,
jumper cables?


01:33.826 --> 01:36.662

Yeah, I think I do.


01:49.942 --> 01:52.412

DANTE: Excuse me, sir.
Dont mean to interrupt.


01:52.444 --> 01:55.548

But I found your wallet.
(chuckles)


01:55.581 --> 01:56.883

Youre a difficult man
to catch up with.


01:56.915 --> 01:58.817

(chuckles) Thank you, man.


01:58.852 --> 02:00.686

This is a big relief.


02:00.719 --> 02:02.588

Sorry about the dirt.


02:02.621 --> 02:04.858

Well see you
later, Mr. Noveer.


02:04.891 --> 02:07.960

My dog, he, uh,
picks things up...
Hmm.


02:07.993 --> 02:10.497

...brings them home
and buries them in our yard.


02:10.530 --> 02:11.965

I tried to clean it off
a little bit,


02:11.997 --> 02:14.533

but couldnt get it all.


02:14.567 --> 02:17.270

Yeah.


02:17.302 --> 02:18.972

(tires squeal)


02:19.004 --> 02:21.608

Didnt mean to interrupt you
and your friends.


02:21.640 --> 02:23.943

Nah, man. You just made
this my lucky day.


02:23.977 --> 02:25.677

(laughs)


02:25.711 --> 02:27.980

Look, man, this is
all I got right now,


02:28.014 --> 02:30.650

but, uh, let me take
you to lunch sometime.


02:30.682 --> 02:33.485

No, man, Im just glad
to get that back to you.


02:33.520 --> 02:35.521

All right, well, let me
take your dog to lunch.


02:35.555 --> 02:37.757

(both laugh)


02:37.789 --> 02:40.460

So, uh, you on your way
to work or something?


02:40.492 --> 02:42.996

Yeah.


02:43.028 --> 02:43.997

Wheres that?


02:44.030 --> 02:45.731

Carl Steel.


02:45.764 --> 02:49.602

(chuckles) Carl Steel.


02:49.635 --> 02:51.003

Hows he to work for?


02:51.037 --> 02:53.639

DANTE: Ah, you know,
h-hes all right.


02:53.673 --> 02:55.775

All right?


02:55.807 --> 02:57.776

He all right to you?


02:57.810 --> 02:59.878

If it wasnt for Carl Steel,
me and my family


02:59.913 --> 03:03.483

wouldve been done-in-for
a long time ago, so...


03:03.515 --> 03:07.453

Is that right?
Yeah.


03:07.486 --> 03:09.021

Well, look,
thanks again, man.


03:09.055 --> 03:10.889

No problem.
Shit, sorry.


03:10.924 --> 03:12.425

(laughs)


03:10.924 --> 03:12.425

You have a good day.


03:12.457 --> 03:13.459

Hey, see you later, now.


03:13.492 --> 03:15.861

Yeah, you, too.


03:13.492 --> 03:15.861

All right.


03:30.810 --> 03:32.812

♪


04:02.842 --> 04:04.843

♪


04:36.475 --> 04:40.545

...which means... youre gonna
have to put off school


04:40.579 --> 04:42.548

for a little while.


04:40.579 --> 04:42.548

For how long?


04:42.581 --> 04:45.884

WILSON: Well, there are, uh,
plenty of colleges right here.


04:45.918 --> 04:47.987

Can we afford those?


04:48.021 --> 04:50.389

I mean the community college.


04:50.423 --> 04:53.925

We are all going to have to
pitch in a little bit.


04:53.959 --> 04:56.428

Why dont we sell something?
Like one of our properties.


04:56.461 --> 05:00.533

We have to sell off
everything, Dannie.


05:00.565 --> 05:02.067

We have to sell the house.


05:03.935 --> 05:05.137

WILSON:
Sweetie, uh,


05:05.170 --> 05:07.072

you are still our priority.


05:07.105 --> 05:08.940

And th-this is an opportunity.


05:08.975 --> 05:11.043

A lot of the kids are taking
this-- the year thing, the...


05:11.076 --> 05:12.545

A gap year.


05:11.076 --> 05:12.545

Yeah, take the gap.


05:12.577 --> 05:14.112

You have to get a job.


05:14.146 --> 05:16.348

(train horn blows)


05:33.199 --> 05:36.069

♪


05:46.579 --> 05:48.081

No, put that away.


05:48.113 --> 05:50.115

Ill be right back.


05:56.855 --> 05:58.091

Mr. Drimmer?


05:58.124 --> 06:01.427

Yeah?


06:01.461 --> 06:03.795

Jake Noveer.
Im a detective.


06:05.732 --> 06:10.536

How long you worked
for Bud Carl?


06:10.569 --> 06:14.040

Uh, you know,
I-I already talked to the cops.


06:14.072 --> 06:15.675

Did the whole, uh,


06:15.708 --> 06:18.144

DNA tests
and everything.


06:18.177 --> 06:20.178

Im just trying
to help you here.


06:20.213 --> 06:22.447

Help me with what?


06:22.481 --> 06:25.584

Well, you seem to do
a lot of things for Mr. Carl.


06:25.617 --> 06:27.887

Materials mover
during the day.


06:27.920 --> 06:29.922

Loading rolls of steel
onto trains at night.


06:29.956 --> 06:31.923

Yeah, well, I got
a little girl to feed.


06:31.957 --> 06:34.793

Here you go.


06:34.826 --> 06:37.562

Ill take any hours
they can give me.


06:37.596 --> 06:38.997

Wheres her mom?


06:40.800 --> 06:43.769

Uh, shes not in
the picture anymore.


06:43.802 --> 06:45.670

A drug thing.


06:45.704 --> 06:48.074

Yeah, I know that
thing pretty well.


06:48.106 --> 06:50.675

Any idea why Bud Carl
is shipping steel


06:50.709 --> 06:52.245

to a Chinese company?


06:52.278 --> 06:56.115

Um, I...


06:56.149 --> 06:59.752

No. I-I dont know anything
about China.


06:59.786 --> 07:02.654

Well, thats where those rolls
you loaded ended up going.


07:02.687 --> 07:05.992

Well, you know, I-I do OT
because I need OT. (chuckles)


07:06.024 --> 07:07.994

Right, right. And when
the cops talked to you,


07:08.026 --> 07:09.629

Im guessing they asked
you about the night


07:09.661 --> 07:10.930

of the Seven Bloods--
where you were.


07:12.932 --> 07:15.901

Yeah, I mean, I told them
I-I was here with her.


07:15.935 --> 07:17.870

Like I said,
Im-Im the only one


07:17.903 --> 07:20.605

that really takes care of her.


07:20.639 --> 07:22.274

Hmm. Well,
I cant ask her,


07:22.307 --> 07:24.677

so you got anybody who
can vouch for that?


07:24.709 --> 07:26.112

You-you want to
talk to someone?


07:26.144 --> 07:28.613

Um... uh, you can talk


07:28.648 --> 07:30.716

to the daycare lady,
Mrs. Bailey.


07:30.750 --> 07:32.584

Bailey, right.


07:30.750 --> 07:32.584

Uh, you know,


07:32.617 --> 07:35.021

I-I picked her up, uh, from work
and I brought her here.


07:35.053 --> 07:37.255

I mean, its not really like
I could, I could, like,


07:37.290 --> 07:38.957

leave her here alone, so...
(chuckles)


07:38.990 --> 07:41.259

And yet you did.


07:44.797 --> 07:47.699

Why do you care about
Bud Carl so much?


07:47.733 --> 07:49.134

What is that supposed to mean?


07:49.168 --> 07:51.103

I know you helped him
that night.


08:01.713 --> 08:03.882

Hey, if-if you know so much,
why dont you just


08:03.915 --> 08:05.151

take me in right now?


08:05.184 --> 08:06.853

Look, heres what I know
happened.


08:06.886 --> 08:09.555

I know you went there
and I know you loaded bodies


08:09.588 --> 08:11.156

in the back of that truck.


08:11.189 --> 08:13.860

I know you helped Bud Carl
get rid of them.


08:13.893 --> 08:16.928

But I didnt see everything,
and to be honest,


08:16.963 --> 08:19.331

I dont think
you killed anybody.


08:19.365 --> 08:22.300

I think youre a good kid
who got caught up in something.


08:24.103 --> 08:25.937

What do you want me to do?


08:25.971 --> 08:28.173

We go down to the police and you
tell them everything you know,


08:28.206 --> 08:31.610

and we find a way to plea
bargain you to freedom.


08:31.644 --> 08:33.712

What does he have on you


08:33.745 --> 08:35.347

that you aint telling me
everything you know right now?


08:35.380 --> 08:37.283

Cause you got
a lot to lose, buddy.


08:37.316 --> 08:40.086

Whyd you go help
him that night?


08:40.119 --> 08:42.687

I didnt.


08:40.119 --> 08:42.687

You did. You know
you did, but why?


08:42.721 --> 08:44.289

Because your boss calls, okay?


08:44.322 --> 08:46.292

But then you get there,
and see all that


08:46.325 --> 08:47.894

and still go through with it?


08:49.028 --> 08:50.696

Why are you
protecting him?


08:50.730 --> 08:54.066

I dont know
what youre talking about.


09:05.811 --> 09:09.215

You know much about
the foster system?


09:09.248 --> 09:11.650

No, no, I dont.


09:11.683 --> 09:13.251

When youre in the foster
system, your chances


09:13.285 --> 09:15.788

of getting adopted
are around ten to 15%.


09:15.821 --> 09:18.924

Now, Im not gonna pretend your
lifes been easy, Mr. Drimmer.


09:20.091 --> 09:23.328

Im sure it really hasnt.


09:23.361 --> 09:27.767

But I am sure you want
a better one for your daughter.


09:27.799 --> 09:29.100

Now, when you dont have someone


09:29.134 --> 09:31.236

that loves you
to take care of you,


09:31.269 --> 09:34.807

every night, you get the idea
that your mom and dad


09:34.840 --> 09:38.878

didnt care enough
to stop you going to jail,


09:38.911 --> 09:42.981

stop you getting hooked
on drugs.


09:43.014 --> 09:44.850

Or you just start to think
that maybe


09:44.884 --> 09:47.919

they didnt want you
in the first place.


09:47.953 --> 09:51.957

And that feeling
doesnt go away.


09:51.990 --> 09:54.726

It stays with you
your whole life.


10:00.365 --> 10:04.235

Yeah. Yeah, I know that feeling.


10:09.341 --> 10:11.344

(train horn blows in distance)


10:15.114 --> 10:17.984

Hey, uh, wh-what
was your name? Jake?


10:18.017 --> 10:21.320

Uh-huh.


10:21.354 --> 10:25.256

Uh, y-you have a father
that was around for you, Jake?


10:25.291 --> 10:28.293

Its weird with
dads, you know?


10:28.326 --> 10:31.797

Sometimes they, they come back
into your life.


10:33.798 --> 10:38.971

Uh, mine seems to be getting me
into a lot of trouble right now.


10:40.072 --> 10:42.040

Yeah?


10:42.073 --> 10:44.110

Yeah.


10:44.143 --> 10:48.880

Get in touch when youre ready
to tell me the whole story.


10:48.913 --> 10:52.018

Itll make it
a lot easier on you.


10:52.051 --> 10:53.351

If you dont,


10:53.385 --> 10:56.855

itll be a lot worse.


10:56.889 --> 10:58.923

Are you still furious at me?


10:58.957 --> 11:00.493

No, of course not.


11:00.525 --> 11:03.495

Im sorry I was nasty to you
about the Garrett thing.


11:03.528 --> 11:05.331

I talked to my therapist
about it, and she said


11:05.364 --> 11:07.466

she thought I was quitting
before I was being fired.


11:07.500 --> 11:09.769

What does that mean?


11:09.802 --> 11:12.738

That I was making up an
excuse to be mad at you


11:12.772 --> 11:17.243

because I was worried about us
losing touch when we go away.


11:17.275 --> 11:19.044

We only have a few more weeks
here left.


11:19.077 --> 11:20.913

I really dont want to spend
them being mad at you.


11:20.946 --> 11:22.914

Thank you.


11:22.947 --> 11:24.417

And Im sorry.


11:24.450 --> 11:26.418

You know,
I was, I was a jerk, too.


11:27.820 --> 11:31.823

So have you heard from him?


11:31.856 --> 11:36.294

Yeah, I... yeah, turns out, we
were completely wrong about him,


11:36.327 --> 11:39.130

and the guy
who beat up Carries mom?


11:39.164 --> 11:41.767

Totally different guy.


11:41.801 --> 11:43.969

Oh, my God.


11:41.801 --> 11:43.969

Were never
gonna talk again,


11:44.003 --> 11:45.971

so yeah, its good.


11:46.004 --> 11:47.405

Im sorry.


11:47.440 --> 11:48.941

Honestly, its for
the best, though.


11:48.974 --> 11:50.275

Im not saying that
because of him.


11:50.308 --> 11:52.144

I just mean, like,
were about to leave


11:52.177 --> 11:55.914

and start this whole new
life and hes staying here.


11:55.947 --> 11:57.917

Yeah.


11:57.950 --> 11:59.951

I mean, you are still excited
about leaving, arent you?


11:59.985 --> 12:02.922

Of course.


12:13.198 --> 12:15.201

(panting)


12:27.513 --> 12:30.048

(dogs barking in distance)


12:34.919 --> 12:36.922

(engine turns off)


12:37.956 --> 12:39.290

BUD:
Whats going on?


12:39.325 --> 12:40.893

I thought the place
would be on fire or something.


12:40.926 --> 12:41.994

Come on.


12:42.027 --> 12:44.330

(barking continues)


12:44.363 --> 12:47.133

GARRETT:<i>
Yeah, a cop was just here.</i>


12:47.165 --> 12:49.835

BUD:<i>
Whatd you say to him?</i>


12:49.869 --> 12:51.036

He-he told me
that he saw me


12:51.070 --> 12:53.105

loading steel rolls
onto a train,


12:53.139 --> 12:56.107

uh, carrying bodies
onto the back of a truck.


12:56.142 --> 12:57.842

How could he see you
carrying bodies


12:57.876 --> 13:00.044

on the back
of that truck?


13:00.078 --> 13:02.280

Theres a camera.


13:04.549 --> 13:06.217

There was a what?


13:06.251 --> 13:08.888

Theres, uh,
theres a camera on the back


13:08.921 --> 13:11.289

of the cube truck.


13:08.921 --> 13:11.289

There wasnt a camera
on the back of that truck.


13:11.322 --> 13:13.091

I dont know what to tell you,
because I found a fucking camera


13:13.125 --> 13:14.092

on the back of the cube truck.


13:14.125 --> 13:16.361

What did you do with it?


13:14.125 --> 13:16.361

I brought it back here.


13:16.394 --> 13:18.230

I-I put it in a drawer,
and its fucking gone now.


13:18.264 --> 13:20.899

Why didnt you tell me
that you had that?


13:20.932 --> 13:22.368

I dont know. I had
other fucking things on my mind


13:22.400 --> 13:24.235

that night.


13:25.270 --> 13:28.006

What was on the tape?


13:30.042 --> 13:32.544

I dont know.


13:30.042 --> 13:32.544

You dont know.


13:32.577 --> 13:34.078

No, I dont know.
I didnt watch it.


13:34.113 --> 13:35.080

You didnt watch it?


13:35.114 --> 13:38.082

I didnt-- I didnt want to.


13:40.019 --> 13:42.321

Yeah,
he also told me that


13:42.354 --> 13:44.190

that steel was going to China.


13:44.222 --> 13:46.392

He said China?


13:44.222 --> 13:46.392

Yeah.


13:46.424 --> 13:49.595

Why the fuck
are you sending steel to China?


13:49.628 --> 13:52.298

You get me
to help you, uh,


13:52.331 --> 13:54.332

clean up bodies.


13:56.969 --> 13:58.937

Just be honest with me.


13:58.971 --> 14:01.005

Its a contract.


14:01.039 --> 14:04.943

Garrett, the contract thats got
the mill running like a top.


14:04.976 --> 14:06.177

Hand to God.


14:06.211 --> 14:10.115

Seven people had to die
because of that?


14:10.149 --> 14:11.583

Our friend, Rick,
and a couple of his buddies


14:11.616 --> 14:13.052

tried to rob us in the middle.


14:13.085 --> 14:15.120

It went to shit.


14:15.153 --> 14:17.523

Guys got killed.


14:17.556 --> 14:20.091

(train horn blows in distance)


14:22.094 --> 14:24.263

Why didnt you go to the cops
with that?


14:27.666 --> 14:29.668

Fuck you, man.


14:34.373 --> 14:38.443

Theyre gonna take me away from
my-my daughter because of you.


14:39.445 --> 14:41.614

Im so sorry.


14:41.647 --> 14:43.148

Im just--


14:43.182 --> 14:46.317

Im-Im so sorry
I got yinz involved.


14:53.692 --> 14:56.195

Ill figure a way
to get you out.


14:56.227 --> 14:59.063

You know, you probably
dont remember this,


14:59.097 --> 15:00.732

but, uh, youd be
out with your mom.


15:00.765 --> 15:02.500

Uh, company picnic.


15:02.533 --> 15:03.568

Grocery store.


15:03.601 --> 15:05.303

And Id come up to you.


15:05.336 --> 15:08.240

Id say, uh,
"How you doing, hotshot?"


15:08.274 --> 15:11.076

Give you a wink, a smile.


15:12.278 --> 15:15.179

I got a lot of regrets.


15:15.214 --> 15:19.217

But not hugging you when I had
the chance, thats, uh...


15:36.467 --> 15:39.337

(truck door closes,
engine starts)


15:43.042 --> 15:44.643

(truck departing)


15:44.677 --> 15:46.644

(beeps)


15:44.677 --> 15:46.644

BUD: Whats going on?


15:46.678 --> 15:48.379

I thought the place would be
on fire or something.


15:48.413 --> 15:50.081

GARRETT:
Come on.


15:50.115 --> 15:53.217

(beeps)


15:53.251 --> 15:55.553

(knocking)


16:02.360 --> 16:04.663

You put a camera on that truck?


16:04.697 --> 16:06.597

Why would you put a camera
on that fucking truck?


16:06.631 --> 16:08.333

(stammers) Once you got
that guy, Rick, involved,


16:08.366 --> 16:09.600

they made me put a camera
in the truck.


16:08.366 --> 16:09.600

They?


16:09.634 --> 16:11.269

Cause he was gonna be with
the money without us around.


16:09.634 --> 16:11.269

They?


16:11.302 --> 16:12.403

Whos in charge of
this operation, huh?


16:12.437 --> 16:13.672

You know that this is
a partnership, man.


16:13.706 --> 16:14.673

Well, thanks to you,


16:14.706 --> 16:16.442

that detective has a tape!


16:16.475 --> 16:17.775

(grunts)


16:17.809 --> 16:20.144

What? Were in this
because of your guy, Rick, man!


16:20.178 --> 16:21.647

He knows about China.
How did he know about China?!


16:21.679 --> 16:23.048

How the fuck would I know that?


16:21.679 --> 16:23.048

You in it with him, huh?


16:23.081 --> 16:24.783

What?


16:23.081 --> 16:24.783

Huh? Are you trying
to set me up?


16:24.817 --> 16:26.317

Is that whats happening?


16:26.351 --> 16:27.653

Wait, if I was trying
to set you up...


16:26.351 --> 16:27.653

Huh?!


16:27.686 --> 16:29.455

...wh-why would I
still be here, man?!


16:29.488 --> 16:32.024

(panting)


16:33.625 --> 16:35.126

Okay.


16:35.159 --> 16:37.462

Okay, okay.


16:37.495 --> 16:39.831

You go to get your guys,


