♪ Ah, ah, ah, ah, ah


35:39.936 --> 35:42.940

♪ Ooh...


35:42.974 --> 35:44.641

(door bells jingle)


35:44.675 --> 35:45.976

Hi.


35:46.010 --> 35:47.577

(door closes)


35:47.612 --> 35:50.447

I called about the job
youd advertised.


35:50.481 --> 35:52.516

Oh, yeah, come on in.


35:52.550 --> 35:55.385

Im Dannie.


35:55.418 --> 35:56.954

Nice to meet you, Dannie.
Im Cass.


35:56.987 --> 35:59.190

Why do you want
to work at a bakery?


36:00.992 --> 36:04.327

Honestly? I dont know
anything about baking...


36:04.362 --> 36:07.998

(chuckles) but Im not going
to college for a while,


36:08.032 --> 36:12.003

and Ive never learned
to do anything direct.


36:12.036 --> 36:15.273

I want to do something
fundamental for a change.


36:16.474 --> 36:18.342

Thats a good answer.


36:20.443 --> 36:22.280

GARRETT:


36:20.443 --> 36:22.280

<i>You want to color
the astronaut blue?</i>


36:22.313 --> 36:25.449

BUD (recorded):
Say, "How you doing, hotshot?"


36:25.483 --> 36:28.920

Give you a wink and a smile.


36:30.721 --> 36:34.525

Got a lot of regrets.


36:34.559 --> 36:36.561

But not hugging you
when I had...


36:47.771 --> 36:49.739

(phone dialing)


36:49.773 --> 36:51.876

(line ringing)


36:51.909 --> 36:54.644

BUD (over phone): Hey.


36:51.909 --> 36:54.644

They didnt get him.


36:54.679 --> 36:56.414

They got busted.


36:56.447 --> 36:57.748

They didnt get the tape.


36:57.782 --> 36:59.784

You need to get out now.


37:04.521 --> 37:06.856

WOMAN:
Uh, theres a...


37:04.521 --> 37:06.856

No, not...


37:06.891 --> 37:08.893

Not now.


37:10.594 --> 37:13.030

(panting)


37:32.382 --> 37:34.385

(bell ringing)


37:37.588 --> 37:38.889

Hey, man.


37:38.922 --> 37:40.757

Can I help you?


37:40.791 --> 37:42.827

Yeah, uh, Im here
to see Bud Carl.


37:42.860 --> 37:44.362

Names Jake Noveer.


37:44.394 --> 37:45.695

Whats it about?


37:45.730 --> 37:47.063

Im a detective.


37:47.097 --> 37:49.300

(rock music playing faintly)


37:52.570 --> 37:54.572

(phone ringing)


38:02.713 --> 38:04.849

Bud Carl.


38:02.713 --> 38:04.849

JIMMY: Hey, Pop.


38:04.882 --> 38:07.018

I-I got a Jake Noveer here
to see you.


38:07.050 --> 38:08.585

Says hes a detective.


38:10.621 --> 38:12.623

Be right there.


38:25.869 --> 38:28.572

(door opens)


38:28.606 --> 38:30.474

Mr. Noveer?


38:30.507 --> 38:32.909

Uh, thanks, Jimmy.


38:32.943 --> 38:35.646

Follow me, please.


38:40.851 --> 38:43.454

And, uh, what can I do for you?


38:43.487 --> 38:46.657

Well, I got some information,
so I wanted to come right over.


38:46.690 --> 38:49.492

Ive never had a problem
with you, Mr. Carl.


38:49.527 --> 38:53.530

Youve employed a lot of people
I care about over the years.


38:53.563 --> 38:55.532

Well, thats
good to hear.


38:55.565 --> 38:57.967

Mr. Carl, I have
footage of you,


38:58.001 --> 39:01.005

Rick Mitchell,
Garrett Drimmer.


39:03.907 --> 39:05.876

Hey, Jimmy.


39:05.909 --> 39:08.411

Two coffees.


39:08.445 --> 39:11.782

And I didnt fully know why,
or what you were up to,


39:11.815 --> 39:16.554

but... then I found this.


39:18.456 --> 39:20.958

Now, Ive been thinking
about how to handle this.


39:20.990 --> 39:23.494

After all, Im a detective,
not a cop,


39:23.527 --> 39:26.831

so we can be
a little more creative.


39:26.864 --> 39:29.532

Creative.


39:29.567 --> 39:31.534

What do you want, money?


39:31.568 --> 39:32.869

Listen,


39:32.902 --> 39:35.206

Mr. Carl, this can go
one of two ways:


39:35.239 --> 39:39.610

you can deny all this and I hand
everything over to the cops.


39:39.643 --> 39:43.514

Theyll investigate,
and this will be real hard.


39:43.547 --> 39:45.682

Theyll shut down the
mill in the process.


39:45.715 --> 39:47.918

Or you can walk
into the Braden PD


39:47.952 --> 39:49.652

on your own volition
and confess.


39:49.686 --> 39:51.789

And why would I do that?


39:51.822 --> 39:54.992

Because I think youre
about to lose everything.


39:55.025 --> 39:57.795

They find out about the murder,


39:57.827 --> 40:01.731

they find out about
your involvement, and this...


40:01.766 --> 40:03.233

But we find a way to keep


40:03.266 --> 40:04.934

the deal you made quiet
so the mill can stay open.


40:04.969 --> 40:07.070

You got a green piece of cloth,
and I dont know


40:07.103 --> 40:08.838

what youre talking about...


40:07.103 --> 40:08.838

Dont fuck with
me on this, Bud.


40:08.873 --> 40:11.708

You understand?
You killed a man.


40:11.742 --> 40:14.545

And this harebrained fucking
get-rich-quick scheme of yours


40:14.577 --> 40:16.880

caused six other people to die.


40:18.581 --> 40:20.483

This is bigger than you.


40:20.518 --> 40:22.152

Look around.


40:22.186 --> 40:24.021

Now, Im doing something
Ive never done before,


40:24.054 --> 40:26.791

which is compromise,
but not for you.


40:26.824 --> 40:30.561

But so all these good people
can keep the jobs that you


40:30.594 --> 40:33.731

and your father
and your grandfather


40:33.764 --> 40:35.965

worked all these years
to provide.


40:40.704 --> 40:43.206

Youre from here, right?


40:43.239 --> 40:46.577

Well, then you know.


40:46.610 --> 40:50.614

See, the Carls lived in Braden.


40:50.648 --> 40:52.949

We gave back.


40:52.983 --> 40:55.786

We-we took responsibility.


40:55.820 --> 40:57.755

I went to school
with the workers kids


40:57.788 --> 41:01.157

and the accountants kids,
the foremans kids.


41:01.192 --> 41:04.260

See, a bosss life
was something you could see.


41:04.295 --> 41:06.864

Something to aspire to.


41:06.896 --> 41:10.867

It wasnt some
get-rich-quick scheme.


41:10.900 --> 41:13.003

I dont know
when it changed.


41:14.204 --> 41:16.106

I dont know.


41:16.139 --> 41:18.576

Maybe when it was...


41:18.608 --> 41:22.579

the bosses living further
and further away and...


41:22.612 --> 41:25.782

nobody in these towns seem
like people to them anymore.


41:28.619 --> 41:31.288

But theyve always
been people to me.


41:34.057 --> 41:36.594

Even the ones who died here.


41:36.626 --> 41:40.831

If you care about the
people, turn yourself in,


41:40.864 --> 41:44.702

so your son can be free
and clear,


41:44.735 --> 41:47.070

and take care
of your granddaughter.


41:47.103 --> 41:50.206

You got till 5:00


41:50.240 --> 41:54.811

today to hand yourself in
to the Braden Police,


41:54.844 --> 41:57.882

or I go there
and show them everything.


42:09.860 --> 42:10.994

(birds chirping)


42:11.027 --> 42:13.030

(vehicle approaches)


42:33.150 --> 42:34.952

Hi.


42:34.985 --> 42:37.987

Dont worry about me.


42:38.021 --> 42:39.690

Hi.
Hi.


42:39.722 --> 42:41.224

Its really
coming together.


42:41.257 --> 42:43.260

Yeah. How was the job interview?


42:43.293 --> 42:44.628

Oh, it was good.


42:44.661 --> 42:46.697

I think I got it.


42:46.730 --> 42:48.632

(gasps)
Good for you.


42:48.666 --> 42:50.367

(doorbell buzzing)


42:48.666 --> 42:50.367

Thanks. Dad?


42:50.400 --> 42:52.068

WILSON:
What?
Dad.


42:52.101 --> 42:53.137

Get the door.


42:53.170 --> 42:54.304

Wh-What?


42:54.338 --> 42:57.907

Why do I always have to...?


43:03.414 --> 43:07.717

You. You upgraded.


43:07.751 --> 43:09.286

You got a bigger wagon.


43:09.320 --> 43:11.355

You...


43:09.320 --> 43:11.355

Downgraded.


43:11.387 --> 43:13.190

This is your house?


43:13.222 --> 43:14.724

Dont judge.


43:14.757 --> 43:16.927

So, whats your story?


43:16.960 --> 43:20.431

Well, Moms still
in the hospital,


43:20.463 --> 43:23.233

and they still cant find Dad.


43:23.266 --> 43:25.101

Oh, thats good, thats good.


43:25.135 --> 43:28.304

But I did get accepted
into the National Science Fair.


43:28.338 --> 43:29.405

When is it?


43:29.440 --> 43:31.275

Where?


43:29.440 --> 43:31.275

October. Phoenix, Arizona.


43:31.307 --> 43:32.775

Whats your project?


43:31.307 --> 43:32.775

Desalinating water.


43:32.809 --> 43:34.411

Why?


43:32.809 --> 43:34.411

Global warming.


43:34.445 --> 43:36.947

People in coastal areas during
hurricanes will need clean water


43:36.981 --> 43:39.248

in order to survive,
before help arrives.


43:39.282 --> 43:40.717

How much are your sculptures?


43:40.751 --> 43:43.387

One for seven, two for 12.


43:43.420 --> 43:46.222

Uh-huh. Yeah, thats good.


43:46.255 --> 43:47.925

Yeah, thats good. Impressive.


43:47.958 --> 43:49.393

(door opens)


43:49.425 --> 43:51.427

Hey, wait. Arent you gonna
buy a sculpture?


43:52.829 --> 43:57.367

Oh, no. Im broke.


43:57.400 --> 44:01.204

(knocking on door)


44:01.237 --> 44:03.106

(knocking continues)


44:13.384 --> 44:15.719

Youre a hard man
to get ahold of.


44:15.753 --> 44:18.021

Was starting to think
you were ducking me.


44:18.054 --> 44:20.456

Oh, yeah, man. Sorry.


44:20.490 --> 44:22.326

Come on in.


44:22.358 --> 44:24.061

As promised.


44:25.262 --> 44:27.764

Now I just need
that painting.


44:31.235 --> 44:34.304

Yeah, uh, you know, its weird.


44:34.338 --> 44:36.005

Its kind of grown on me.


44:36.039 --> 44:38.041

I can just take that instead.


44:38.074 --> 44:40.043

(chuckles)


44:40.077 --> 44:42.780

That paintings
worth $2 million.


44:42.813 --> 44:44.414

You said one.


44:44.447 --> 44:48.418

Yeah, well,
its got sentimental value.


44:48.452 --> 44:50.954

Its been with me
since I was a kid.


44:57.360 --> 45:00.063

Ill give you two for it.


45:03.032 --> 45:07.438

Theres 1.2 in there, in cash,


45:07.471 --> 45:09.306

and you can keep your check.


45:09.338 --> 45:14.210

Do you always keep this
kind of cash laying around?


45:14.244 --> 45:18.815

Come on.
We got a deal?


45:18.849 --> 45:20.851

♪


45:26.824 --> 45:29.226

So, how did it go?


45:29.259 --> 45:31.494

Holy shit.


45:31.527 --> 45:33.362

Oh, my God.


45:33.396 --> 45:35.032

Whats that one called?


45:35.065 --> 45:36.833

(exhales)


45:36.867 --> 45:40.170

We call it the Accordion Con.


45:40.204 --> 45:42.539

Well, thats a good one.


46:04.161 --> 46:07.130

How are you? Is the
chief in by any chance?


46:07.164 --> 46:09.132

LORI: Uh, yes. Hes
back in his office.


46:09.166 --> 46:11.168

Okay, thank you.


46:29.119 --> 46:31.355

Chief Trask,


46:31.387 --> 46:33.556

my clients prepared
to clear up all matters


46:33.590 --> 46:37.226

regarding the Seven
Bloods incident.


46:37.260 --> 46:40.130

Hes prepared to confess
to a series of crimes


46:40.164 --> 46:41.632

that will give you
a clear picture


46:41.664 --> 46:45.568

of the incident
from beginning to end.


46:45.601 --> 46:47.570

In exchange for
his confession,


46:47.603 --> 46:50.306

he has some stipulations.


47:02.686 --> 47:04.887

(door closes)


47:08.291 --> 47:10.260

♪ Shes climbed aboard that
midnight train ♪


47:10.293 --> 47:12.094

♪ The marches will never stop


47:12.128 --> 47:14.398

♪ I guess I shouldve
spoke up... ♪


47:14.431 --> 47:16.266

Hey, Robyn.
Hey, Chewy.


47:16.300 --> 47:21.170

♪ Oh, oh, oh...


47:21.204 --> 47:23.673

Hey, man. Let me buy you a beer.


47:23.706 --> 47:25.943

♪ If Id thought
shed needed to know... ♪


47:25.976 --> 47:27.610

What do you want, dude?


47:27.643 --> 47:30.246

I dont want anything,
I just want to buy you a beer.


47:30.280 --> 47:34.684

♪ Id never let her go...


47:34.717 --> 47:38.521

Im good.


47:38.554 --> 47:40.389

Hey, Walmart.


47:40.423 --> 47:43.193

Do you think Im a racist?


47:43.226 --> 47:44.628

Uh, yeah, dude.


47:44.661 --> 47:47.164

(laughs)


47:44.661 --> 47:47.164

Man, why would
you say that to me?


47:47.197 --> 47:48.931

Cause youre
fucking racist, Chewy.


47:54.438 --> 47:56.405

ROBYN:
What can I get you?


47:56.440 --> 47:59.610

Um...


47:56.440 --> 47:59.610

Just get him whatever
he wants, on my tab.


47:59.643 --> 48:02.144

From the well.


48:02.179 --> 48:04.447

Brown or clear?


48:04.481 --> 48:07.985

Brown.


48:08.018 --> 48:12.289

(ringtone playing)


48:12.322 --> 48:15.192

Hello?


48:12.322 --> 48:15.192

Hey, Terri. Its Peter Trask.


48:15.224 --> 48:17.327

Hey, uh, whats,
whats going on?


48:17.360 --> 48:19.329

We have some new information
about the case.


48:19.362 --> 48:22.032

Um, would you mind coming down
to the station


48:22.065 --> 48:23.699

so we can talk about it
in person?


48:23.733 --> 48:25.534

Yeah, Ill-Ill be,
Ill be right there.


48:25.568 --> 48:29.606

I just dont want to be
that guy. I really dont.


48:29.639 --> 48:31.141

So dont.


48:31.173 --> 48:34.010

(chuckles)
Its really that easy.


48:34.043 --> 48:36.346

Right.


48:36.380 --> 48:39.148

(exhales)


48:39.181 --> 48:42.018

Hey, can you, uh...


48:42.052 --> 48:44.387

can you come to the
police station with me?


48:44.420 --> 48:46.322

Uh, the chief just
called and said


48:46.356 --> 48:48.125

theres some break
in the case.


48:48.157 --> 48:51.193

So, I mean, I would ask
Robyn, but shes got to work.


48:51.228 --> 48:53.597

Yeah. Yeah, of course.


48:51.228 --> 48:53.597

Yeah.


48:53.630 --> 48:57.300

Okay.


48:57.333 --> 48:59.503

Come on, dumbass.


48:59.536 --> 49:02.105

Fuck it.


49:06.443 --> 49:08.144

Guys are saying
it was Bud.


49:20.090 --> 49:22.992

(Terri crying)


49:25.295 --> 49:27.297

(speaks indistinctly)


49:32.101 --> 49:34.070

TRASK:<i>
Ladies and gentlemen,</i>


49:34.103 --> 49:37.340

weve had a break in the case
of the murders at the mill.


49:37.373 --> 49:39.342

Uh, were still investigating


49:39.376 --> 49:42.211

based on the information
we received,


49:42.244 --> 49:44.715

but today, a local businessman


49:44.748 --> 49:49.652

and a man whos done a lot of
good for this town, Bud Carl...


49:49.686 --> 49:51.355

(people murmuring)


49:51.387 --> 49:53.757

...confessed to involvement
in the crime,


49:53.789 --> 49:58.762

as well as the murder
of Rick Mitchell.


49:58.795 --> 50:02.298

Apparently, Mr. Carl was part of
an illegal counterfeiting ring,


50:02.331 --> 50:04.367

which he led with outside help


50:04.400 --> 50:08.804

from a man were still
looking for, Michael Goodman.


50:08.838 --> 50:10.806

If anyone has any information
about this man, please contact


50:10.840 --> 50:15.679

the Braden or state police
department immediately.


50:15.711 --> 50:17.380

In carrying this out,


50:17.414 --> 50:21.117

Mr. Carl admits that
he ultimately lost sight


50:21.150 --> 50:23.619

of his connection
to his community.


50:23.652 --> 50:27.623

At this point in time,
Carl Steel will remain open,


50:27.657 --> 50:30.427

uh, until further notice.
Thank you.


50:30.460 --> 50:32.461

(overlapping chatter)


50:39.402 --> 50:41.704

Bird?


50:46.309 --> 50:48.612

(train horn blows in distance)


51:15.605 --> 51:17.606

♪


51:47.670 --> 51:49.672

♪


52:03.753 --> 52:05.554

(grunts softly)


52:09.626 --> 52:11.594

Thought that was
your file cabinet.


52:11.628 --> 52:14.563

Its pretty comfortable.
You should try it.


52:17.567 --> 52:19.702

Youre actually ready
to use this thing?


52:19.735 --> 52:21.737

Maybe.


52:27.476 --> 52:31.947

♪ Everybodys gotta live


52:31.981 --> 52:37.219

♪ And everybodys gonna die


52:37.253 --> 52:41.690

♪ Everybodys gotta live...


52:41.724 --> 52:44.393

Fuck him.


52:41.724 --> 52:44.393

Yeah, fuck him, but...


52:44.427 --> 52:46.762

But what? He killed our friend.


52:46.795 --> 52:51.434

Yeah, thats right. And now,
now hes gonna pay for it.


52:51.467 --> 52:53.235

You think hes gonna get
the death penalty?


52:53.269 --> 52:56.005

Life without parole, I bet.
Whats your best guess?


52:56.039 --> 52:57.940

30 years.
Hell probably get 30 years.


52:57.974 --> 52:59.809

JONNO:
His last 30.


52:59.842 --> 53:03.679

Nobody has any idea
how this things gonna land.


53:03.713 --> 53:06.315

TERRI: What do you mean,
with the mill?


53:06.349 --> 53:07.650

The whole thing.


53:07.684 --> 53:10.452

Well, Im going home.


53:10.487 --> 53:12.289

Robyn, can you close me out?


53:12.322 --> 53:13.989

I got these two guys, too.


53:12.322 --> 53:13.989

WALMART:
Thanks, Terri.


53:14.023 --> 53:16.492

Mm-hmm.


53:14.023 --> 53:16.492

Heres some cash for you, Terri.


53:16.525 --> 53:17.927

No, no. Fuck off with that.


53:16.525 --> 53:17.927

39.


53:17.960 --> 53:20.262

Thank you.


53:20.297 --> 53:25.467

Hey, man, it was
great meeting you.


53:25.501 --> 53:30.507

Um, lets grab a drink
or something, you know?


53:30.539 --> 53:32.976

Yeah.
Yeah?


53:33.009 --> 53:34.610

Yeah.
Cool.


53:34.643 --> 53:36.646

TERRI:
I owe you this.


53:36.679 --> 53:40.449

(quietly):
Keep it.


53:40.483 --> 53:43.253

Hey, Ill, Ill walk you out?


53:44.454 --> 53:46.422

Okay.


53:46.456 --> 53:47.757

Cool.


53:47.791 --> 53:51.494

ROBYN: Bye, Chewy.
Bye, Terri.


53:53.597 --> 53:55.599

(doorbell rings)


54:01.771 --> 54:03.773

Hey.


54:04.974 --> 54:07.677

Hey.


54:07.710 --> 54:10.713

I dont like the way
we left things.


54:11.880 --> 54:14.351

Want to come in?


54:16.920 --> 54:20.623

Yeah, I was just making,
uh, some, uh, dinner.


54:20.657 --> 54:23.326

Hi, pretty girl.
Whatcha got?


54:23.360 --> 54:24.494

(gasps)


54:24.527 --> 54:26.528

Are you hiding?


54:30.967 --> 54:35.472

I-I thought youd be, like,
um, at college by now.


54:35.505 --> 54:38.842

Yeah, uh...


54:38.875 --> 54:44.447

um... Im not going.


54:44.481 --> 54:47.684

Why?


54:44.481 --> 54:47.684

Funding fell through,


54:47.717 --> 54:51.755

so Im gonna take a year
and work, I guess.


54:51.788 --> 54:53.757

What, do you, like,
need a job or-or, uh...?


54:53.789 --> 54:54.923

(chuckles)


54:54.958 --> 54:56.960

I just, I figured


54:56.992 --> 55:01.498

that since Im not going,


55:01.530 --> 55:04.867

we could... hang out?


55:16.913 --> 55:18.914

(laughs softly)


55:21.483 --> 55:24.788

Um...


55:21.483 --> 55:24.788

(timer dings)


55:24.820 --> 55:28.791

You want to, like, I dont know,
do you want to stay for...


55:28.824 --> 55:30.126

(Carrie babbles)


55:30.159 --> 55:31.827

You want to stay
for dinner, or...?


55:31.860 --> 55:33.963

Yeah. No, dinner sounds great.


55:33.996 --> 55:36.599

Hey, Jake.


55:36.632 --> 55:38.702

JAKE:
Chief Trask.


55:38.735 --> 55:39.869

Thanks for coming down.


55:39.902 --> 55:42.871

Of course.


55:42.905 --> 55:45.875

